            <li class="list-unstyled">Ingredients:
              <ul>
                <li> 4 cups of flour </li>
                <li> 4 teaspoons of baking powder</li>
                <li> ½ teaspoon of salt</li>
                <li> 1 cup of unsalted butter  </li>
                <li> 1 cup of heavy cream </li>
                <li> ½ teaspoon of vanilla extract</li>
                <li> 1 ½ cups of berries</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <p></p>
            <p> Preparation: </p>
            Combine all the ingredients in the above order. 
            Start with the dry mix, followed by the cold butter. 
            I recommend using a manual whisk. Stir in heavy cream and vanilla into the mixture and once you have a dough texture incorporate the berries. 
            Finally divide the dough into even “rock” pieces.
